%%{init: {'theme': 'base', 'themeVariables': {'actorBkg': '#E8F5E9', 'actorBorder': '#2E7D32', 'signalColor': '#333333', 'fontSize': '13px'}}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as OAuth Client
    participant TE as Token Endpoint
    participant CAM as Client Auth<br/>Middleware
    participant GH as Refresh Token<br/>Grant Handler
    participant TV as Token Validator
    participant TS as Token Service

    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
        C->>TE: POST /oauth2/token<br/>grant_type=refresh_token<br/>refresh_token=...&scope=...<br/>+ Client authentication
    end

    rect rgb(243, 229, 245)
        TE->>CAM: Client Auth Middleware
        CAM-->>TE: Client authenticated

        Note over TE: Validate refresh_token<br/>grant allowed for app
        TE->>GH: ValidateGrant + HandleGrant

        GH->>TV: ValidateRefreshToken(token, clientID)
        Note over TV: Verify JWT signature + expiry<br/>Validate sub == client_id<br/>Validate required claims present

        TV-->>GH: Refresh token claims

        Note over GH: Scope intersection:<br/>requested scopes intersect original<br/>(cannot escalate)

        alt renew_on_grant = true
            Note over GH: Rotate: issue new<br/>refresh token
        else renew_on_grant = false
            Note over GH: Reuse existing<br/>refresh token
        end

        GH->>TS: BuildAccessToken<br/>(+ optional new refresh token)
        TS-->>GH: Tokens

        GH-->>TE: Token response
        TE-->>C: 200 OK<br/>{ access_token, refresh_token?,<br/>  expires_in }<br/>Cache-Control: no-store
    end
